<span id="freeTextContainer559854873276602503">Ok. After much deliberation, I&apos;ve come to the conclusion that I was very glad I gave this a shot...,finally! When I first became interested in reading a little more extreme horror I was very reluctant to dip into topics that might offend me. If u read this book, you know that it does have scenes of sexual abuse of a minor or minors. Bothered me and still does, but after reading jack Ketchum&apos;s Stranglehold, I figured I could handle it. Stranglehold was far more difficult to read than this. Now, t</span>
  <span id="freeText559854873276602503" style="display:none">Ok. After much deliberation, I've come to the conclusion that I was very glad I gave this a shot...,finally! When I first became interested in reading a little more extreme horror I was very reluctant to dip into topics that might offend me. If u read this book, you know that it does have scenes of sexual abuse of a minor or minors. Bothered me and still does, but after reading jack Ketchum's Stranglehold, I figured I could handle it. Stranglehold was far more difficult to read than this. Now, that I got that out, this book was pretty good. The best parts for me being the beast and the diary that unfolded the mystery of how he became. The ending was a tad disappointing, but surprised me as I wanted a different outcome. I hope to be revisited by unsaid characters in The Beast House. Disturbing but somehow enjoyable....;)</span>
